== 延伸阅读 ==
* Charles Blattberg, ''From Pluralist to Patriotic Politics: Putting Practice First'', Oxford University Press, 2000. ISBN 978-0-19-829688-1.
* Craig Calhoun, ''Is it Time to Be Postnational?'', in ''Ethnicity, Nationalism, and Minority Rights'', (eds.）Stephen May, Tariq Modood and Judith Squires. Cambridge: Cambridge UP, 2004. pp 231–256. Online at [http://www.ssrc.org/programs/calhoun/publications/TimetoBePostnational.pdf www.ssrc.org] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ssrc.org/programs/calhoun/publications/TimetoBePostnational.pdf |date=20061107225021 }}.
* Paul Gomberg, “Patriotism is Like Racism,” in Igor Primoratz, ed., ''Patriotism'', Humanity Books, 2002, pp. 105–112. ISBN 978-1-57392-955-4.
* Jürgen Habermas, “Appendix II: Citizenship and National Identity,” in ''Between Facts and Norms: Contributions to a Discourse Theory of Law and Democracy'', trans. William Rehg, MIT Press, 1996.
* Alasdair MacIntyre, 'Is Patriotism a Virtue?', in: R. Beiner (ed.）, ''Theorizing Citizenship'', 1995, State University of New York Press, pp. 209 – 228.
* Joshua Cohen and Martha C. Nussbaum, ''For Love of Country: Debating the Limits of Patriotism'', Beacon Press, 1996. ISBN 978-0-8070-4313-4.
* George Orwell, “[http://www.orwell.ru/library/essays/nationalism/english/e_nat Notes on Nationalism] {{Wayback|url=http://www.orwell.ru/library/essays/nationalism/english/e_nat |date=20130120035738 }},” in ''England Your England and Other Essays'', Secker and Warburg, 1953.
* Igor Primoratz, ed., ''Patriotism'', Humanity Books, 2002. ISBN 978-1-57392-955-4.
* Daniel Bar-Tal and Ervin Staub, ''Patriotism'', Wadsworth Publishing, 1999. ISBN 978-0-8304-1410-9.
* Maurizio Viroli, ''For Love of Country: An Essay on Patriotism and Nationalism'', Oxford University Press, 1997. ISBN 978-0-19-829358-3.

